                      <h2><center>HOW IT WORKS</center></h2>
           
  <p style="line-height:28px;margin:20px 0px">Upon registering with EMDB, the candidates are assigned with an unique EMDB ID against which they update their availability status. The same ID is also mentioned on the profiles that they uploaded into the EMDB system. When recruiters get access to a desired profile from EMDB, they can use the EMDB ID mentioned on it to track the availability status of the candidate. This avoids the need to connect with the unavailable candidates and saves valuable time of the recruiters that can be further utilized on screening available candidates.</p>
				 
